exercises.text:
Review the definitions of the following concepts:

(a) Key predistribution;

(b) Session key distribution;

(c) Key agreement;

(d) Kerberos;

(e) Post-quantum cryptography;

(f) Learning with errors.

Discuss the advantages and disadvantages of using key predistribution, session key distribution and key agreement protocols in the following scenarios:

(a) A corporate network such as NTNU's Intranet;

(b) A small company or domestic environment;

(c) Internet communications (e.g. HTTPS, secure email).
